					<section id="design">
						<div class="page-header">
							<h1>Customization <small>all about design</small></h1> <a href="#" class="scroller pull-right"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
						</div>
						<h3 class="m2" >Font</h3>
						<p>This template use "Open Sans" for the container and "pacifico" for some heading. But if you want to change the fonts:</p>
						<ol>
						<li>Go to google fonts website,</li>
						<li>then choose your font, go to “quick use” and copy this line (ctrl + c),</li>
						<li>past this line on the header (<code>header.php</code>) of the template (line 31).</li>
						<li>Go to <code>style.css</code> find the lines where you want to change the font ( font-family: ...) and copy the name of your new font. To save time, most publishers has a text replacement tool( ctrl + h).
						</ol>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Background</h3>
						<p>Its very easy ! The backgrounds are in the folder "<code>images/backgrounds/</code>", choose yours. Then in <code>style.css</code>, line 14 replace "1" by "your_number".</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Color</h3>
						<p>All the colors of the template are managed by the stylesheet and not by color images. Thus, it is very simple change the color of the background, text, icons managed by some layers ... <br />
                        So open <code> style.css</code> and simply replace all <code>#00afff</code> with your color (you can find your color in the right format on <a href="http://www.colorpicker.com" target="_blank"> Color Picker </a>).
						The only complication is that there are 2 gradients (menu list and table pricing) and it takes 2 other colors for these gradients (So find your own color with Colorpicker)...(lines 195-200, 518-523 in style.css replace with your own, you probably need to change the border color too, just above them).
                        </p> 
                        <div class="alert alert-info">
                            <p>To save time, most publishers has a text replacement tool ( ctrl + h).</p>
                        </div>
                        <p>Otherwise, 10 color themes are available (<code>css -> style_...</code>) You just have to deflect the link (in the tag: <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>):</p>
                        <pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" type='text/css'&gt;</pre>
                        <p>With:</p>
                        <pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style_yourColor.css" type='text/css'&gt;</pre>
										
						<h3 class="m2" >Logo</h3>
						<p>Size recommended is <strong>200x62</strong>px, just have to resize your logo at the good size and past it in the folder <code>images</code> then call it <code>logo.png</code>.</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Favicon</h3>
						<p>Create your favicon <a href="http://www.favicon.cc/" target="_blank">here</a>, then past it in the folder <code>images</code> then call it <code>favicon.png</code></p>
						<div class="alert alert-info">
                            <p><strong>Favicon:</strong><br />A favicon(short for Favorite icon), also known as a shortcut icon, Web site icon, URL icon, or bookmark icon, is a file containing one or more small icons, most commonly 16×16 pixels, associated with a particular Web site or Web page. A web designer can create such an icon and install it into a Web site (or Web page) by several means, and graphical web browsers will then make use of it. Browsers that provide favicon support typically display a page's favicon in the browser's address bar and next to the page's name in a list of bookmarks. Browsers that support a tabbed document interface typically show a page's favicon next to the page's title on the tab, and site-specific browsers use the favicon as desktop icon. (from Wikipedia)</p>
                        </div>
					</section>
					<!--///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					PHP template
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////-->
					<section id="php">
						<div class="page-header">
							<h1>PHP templates <small>how it working</small></h1> <a href="#" class="scroller pull-right"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
						</div>
						<p>The php template is a set of .php with the same building these are "models". They represent only the container (with your page's content), the top and the footer are the same for all the pages so it's the same file ! What does it change? Productivity, timing...compared to. html. <u>Example:</u> if you want to change your menu: in the html template you have to open each files and change it (20 times because there are 20 files...) whereas, with the .php template just have to change it in header.php and it'll be ready for each files (1 time)</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Header.php</h3>
						<p>This file containing the <strong>stylesheets</strong>, the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>, <strong>hidden area</strong>, the <strong>logo</strong>, the <strong>slogan</strong> and the <strong>menu</strong>. Just have to open it and replace with your own settings, the change will be ready for all your website. See: <a href="#design">#customization</a>, <a href="#social">#social</a></p>
						<h4>Hidden area</h4>
						<p>You've probably seen the arrow on the top right corner. When you click on it, a hidden area appears. You can display here your phone, a welcome message, your social icons... </p>
						<h4>Menu</h4>
						<div class="alert alert-error">
                            <p><strong>Warning !</strong><br />Don't forgotten, when you add or delete a page, refresh your menu (delete or add a link).</p>
                        </div>
						<h4>Logo and slogan</h4>
						<p>Don't forgotten to add your logo and your slogan, it's your website, not mine show it ! ;)</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Footer.php</h3>
						<p>This file containing the <strong>javascript files</strong>, the <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>, <strong>bottom widgets</strong>, the <strong>bottom menu</strong>, the <strong>social icons</strong> and the <strong>footer</strong>. Just have to open it and replace with your own settings, the change will be ready for all your website.
						See: <a href="#design">#customization</a>, <a href="#social">#social</a>, <a href="#credits">#credits</a>, <a href="#sliders">#sliders</a></p>
						<h4>Widgets (bottom area)</h4>
						<p>This area is here to add more informations(tweets, news, conatct), display your last tweets, your address and your last news.</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Sidebar.php</h3>
						<p>This file containing the <strong>sidebar</strong> displaying in the <code>blog.php</code> and <code>single_post.php</code> but you're free to include it in other pages.</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Slider_1.php</h3>
						<p>This file containing the content of the slider 1 (home page 3), see "<a href="#sliders">slider part</a>" for more informations. Why this file ? because with it, you just have to include it as in <code>home3.php</code> in <code>&lt;section id="wrapper_slider"</code> to display your slider...
						See: <a href="#design">#customization</a>, <a href="#sliders">#sliders</a></p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Slider_2.php</h3>
						<p>This file containing the content of the slider 2 (home page 4), see "<a href="#sliders">slider part</a>" for more informations. Why this file ? because with it, you just have to include it as in <code>home4.php</code> in <code>&lt;section id="wrapper_slider"</code> to display your slider...
						See: <a href="#design">#customization</a>, <a href="#sliders">#sliders</a></p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Slider_last_projects.php</h3>
						<p>This file containing the content of the last projects slider (index, home2, home3, single project, 404 error), see "<a href="#sliders">slider part</a>" for more informations. Why this file ? because once set, you just have to include it as in <code>index.php</code> in <code>&lt;div class="span12 m1   last_projects"</code> to display your latest projects in the pages of your choices. Magic !
						See: <a href="#design">#customization</a>, <a href="#sliders">#sliders</a></p>
					</section>
					<!--///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					New page
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////-->
					<section id="new-page">
						<div class="page-header">
							<h1>New page</h1> <a href="#" class="scroller pull-right"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
						</div>
						<h3 class="m2" >With the php template</h3>
						<p>Follow these instructions:</p>
						<ol>
							<li>Open <code>template.php</code></li>
							<li>Read the comments</li>
							<li>Put you page name <code>line 8</code></li>
							<li>Put the page description and the keywords <code>lines 13, 14</code></li>
							<li>Put your content <code>line 66</code>, see: <a href="#bootstrap">#bootstrap</a></li>
							<li>Save as <code>yourpage.php</code></li>
							<li>Open <code>header.php</code></li>
							<li>Add a link where you want in the menu that goes to your new page
								<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="yourpage.php"&gt;New page name&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</pre>
							</li>
						</ol>
						<h3 class="m2" >With the html template</h3>
						<p>Follow these instructions:</p>
						<ol>
							<li>Open a new page in your text editor</li>
							<li>Copy a the containing of <code>template.html</code></li>
							<li>Replace all the "Page name" or "title here" with your page name</li>
							<li>Put the page description and the keywords <code>lines 7, 8</code></li>
							<li>Put your content <code>line 171</code>, see: <a href="#bootstrap">#bootstrap</a></li>
							<li>Save as <code>yourpage.html</code></li>
							<li>Open each pages of your website</li>
							<li>Add a link where you want in the menu that goes to your new page
								<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="yourpage.html"&gt;New page name&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</pre>
							</li>
						</ol>
					</section>
					<!--///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					Sliders
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////-->
					<section id="sliders">
						<div class="page-header">
							<h1>Sliders <small>home page, quotes, news</small></h1>  <a href="#" class="scroller pull-right"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
						</div>
						<h3 class="m2" >Home page slider 1</h3>
						<p>Find it in <code>includes/slider_1.php</code>. This slider is working with <code>sequence.jquery-min.js</code>, the settings are in <code>main.js</code> (lines 18->43), the stylesheet of this slider is <code>style_slider.css</code>. See: <a href="#credits">#credits</a></p>
						<h4>Add a new slide</h4>
						<p>Just have to add a new chip as:</p>
						<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;!-- // A slide // --&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h3 class="title  text_shadow"&gt;Slide title&lt;/h3&gt;
    &lt;p class="subtitle  text_shadow"&gt;Text in the slide&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;a class="btn_slider btn btn-success btn-large" href="your link"&gt;&lt;i class=" icon-resize-small icon-white"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Read more&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;img class="model" src="images/images_slider/yourimage.png" alt="Image slide 5 (used for the pagination)" /&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;</pre>
						<p>If you add a new slide add a new <li> with the same "alt" just bellow (see slider_1.php line 62).Or if you want just a slide with image see "Home page slider 2" just bellow.</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Home page slider 2</h3>
						<p>Find it in <code>includes/slider_2.php</code>. This slider is working with <code>slides.min.jquery.js</code>, the settings are in <code>main.js</code> (lines 285->++), the stylesheet of this slider is <code>style_slider.css</code>. See: <a href="#credits">#credits</a></p>
						<h4>Add a new slide</h4>
						<p>Just have to add a new div as:</p>
						<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;div class="slide"&gt;
    &lt;img src="images/images_slider/yourimage.png"&gt;
    &lt;div class="caption"&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;A caption text&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
						<p>If you don't want a caption text delete the div <code>class="caption"</code>.</p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Quotes slider</h3>
						<p>Find it in <code>index.php</code>, <code>home3.php</code>. This slider is working with <code>slides.min.jquery.js</code>, the settings are in <code>main.js</code> (lines 47->76). See: <a href="#credits">#credits</a></p>
						<h4>Add a new quote</h4>
						<p>Just have to add a new chip as:</p>
						<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;!-- // A quote // --&gt;
&lt;div class="quote_slide span12"&gt;
    &lt;cite&gt;‘‘Your quote goes here’’&lt;/cite&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;Author or message goes here.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >News slider</h3>
						<p>Find it in <code>footer.php</code>. This slider is working with <code>slides.min.jquery.js</code>, the settings are in <code>main.js</code> (lines 80->90). See: <a href="#credits">#credits</a></p>
						<h4>Add a new news</h4>
						<p>Just have to add a new div (<code>footer.php</code> line 30) as:</p>
						<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;div&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;12/04/12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;i&gt;
		Line 1&lt;br /&gt; 
		Line 2&lt;br /&gt;
		Line 3&lt;br /&gt;
		&lt;a href="linktothepage"&gt;More...&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;/i&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
						<p>The <code>&lt;br /&gt; </code> are here to retract the text in the bubble. See: <a href="#credits">#credits</a></p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Last project slider</h3>
						<p>Find it in <code>includes/slider_last_projects.php</code>. This slider is working with <code>jquery.elastislide.js</code>, the settings are in <code>main.js</code> (lines 94->99). See: <a href="#credits">#credits</a></p>
						<h4>Add a new news</h4>
						<p>Just have to add a new chip in the files where you found this slider as:</p>
						<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;div class="viewport thumbnail"&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;span class="dark-background"&gt;&lt;a href="http://placehold.it/320x240" class="project_glass" rel="prettyPhoto" &gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="single_project.html" class="project_link"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;img src="http://placehold.it/160x120" alt=""/&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
						<p> See: <a href="#credits">#credits</a></p>
					</section>
