					<!--///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					Contact page
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////-->
					<section id="contact">
						<div class="page-header">
							<h1>Contact page <small>form and map</small></h1> <a href="#" class="scroller pull-right"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
						</div>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Form</h3>
						<p>The contact form needs your email for working, so go at <code>contact.php</code> and line 36: set it</p>
						<p><strong>Issue</strong><br />
						You see a warning of success but you receive nothing:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Check if your provider accepted the sending of emails</li>
							<li>Check if your email is correctly set</li>
							<li>Check your mailbox again...</li>
						</ul>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Map</h3>
						<p>The map is initialized in <code>map.js</code>.
						For the map we need the position of your business. To find it go to:<br />
						<a href="http://itouchmap.com/latlong.html" target="_blank">Itouchmap</a><br />
						A simple click from the site map on the location of your business will give very precise longitude and latitude (for example: 38.941182, -46.625977), copy the result in <code>map.js</code> line 7. Then you can change the default icon (png), create your icon and call it <code>picto_map</code> and copy this icon in the folder <code>images</code>. Then the field <code>Info Windows title</code> is used to add a title to the "bubble" that appears when clicking on the icon and as the name suggests , <code>Info Windows content</code> will inform you content of the "bubble". In order to avoid long texts, an address should be enough.</p>
					</section>
					<!--///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					Portfolio
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////-->
					<section id="portfolio">
						<div class="page-header">
							<h1>Portfolio</h1> <a href="#" class="scroller pull-right"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
						</div>
						<h3 class="m2" >Build your portfolio</h3>
						<ol>
							<li>Choose the number of columns of your future portfolio ...3, 4 or 6</li>
							<li>Open the following file according to your choice(<code>portfolio_3col.php</code>, <code>portfolio_4col.php</code> or <code>portfolio_6col.php</code>)</li>
							<li>You have to find for each project a picture, a description, a thumbnail (See: <a href="#size">#size</a>), few categories, and a date</li>
							<li>For each project add:
							<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;!-- // A Project // --&gt;
	&lt;div class="span3or4or6"&gt;
		&lt;div class="viewport thumbnail four_col your_category your_date"&gt;
            &lt;div&gt;
                &lt;span class="dark-background"&gt;&lt;a href="picture url" class="project_glass" rel="prettyPhoto"  title="Your project name" &gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="your project page" class="project_link"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
                 &lt;img src="thumbnail url" alt="" height="180 -> <a href="#size">#size</a>" width="260 -> <a href="#size">#size</a>"/&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- end .viewport --&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- end .span3or4or6 --&gt;</pre>
							</li>
							<li>Then create a page for each projects, you have to open <code>single_project.php</code> and save as "your project page"</li>
							<li>Do it for each project, you will have all your projects as in the preview, but how to run the filtering ? (just below)</li>
						</ol>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Manage the filtering</h3>
						<p>You have to add for each project a class which symbolizes the category and an other for the date (look at <code>portfolio_4col.php</code> line 97 to see an example). Then, for filter you need some buttons or links as in the preview for that, you have to add: <code>data-filter=".category_name"</code> (look at <code>portfolio_4col.php</code> line 66->91 to see an example)</p>
						<p>More informations here:<br />
						<a class="btn btn-inverse btn-large" href="http://isotope.metafizzy.co/docs/filtering.html" target="_blank"><i class="icon-home icon-white"></i> Filtering documentation</a>
						</p>
					</section>
