						<h3 class="m2" >Progress bars</h3>
						<p>I invite you to look at the documentation of Bootstrap about this topic:<br /><br />
								<a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/components.html#progress" class="btn btn-inverse btn-large" target="_blank"><i class="icon-white icon-ok-sign"></i> Progress bars with Bootstrap</a></p>
						
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Miscellaneous</h3>
						<h5>Margins</h5>
                            <p>For practical reasons, two classes have been added for horizontal spacing. They just need to add them to any elements for a separation with the top element:</p>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="span5">
                                    <h5><code>class="m1"</code></h5>
                                    <p>This class adds a margin to the element: <code>margin-top: 24px</code></p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="span5">
                                    <h5><code>class="m2"</code></h5>
                                        <p>This class adds a margin to the element: <code>margin-top: 48px</code></p>
                                </div>
                            </div><!-- end .row -->
                        <h5>Floating</h5>
                            <p>To place items on the page (left or right), 2 classes were created by Bootstrap:</p>
                                    <div class="row">
                                        <div class="span5">
                                            <strong>pull-left <code>class="pull-left"</code></strong>
                                            <p>This class places the item on the left of its container with the float property: <code>float: left</code></p>
                                            <strong>Example</strong><br />
                                            <a class="btn btn-danger pull-left clearfix" href="#" style="margin-right: 8px;"> A button with pull left</a>
                                            <a class="btn btn-danger" href="#"> A button</a>
                                            <pre class="prettyprint linenums m1" style="margin-bottom: 18px;">&lt;a class="btn btn-danger pull-left" href="#"&gt; A button with pull-left&lt;/a&gt;</pre>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="span5">
                                            <strong>pull-right <code>class="pull-right"</code></strong>
                                            <p>This class places the item on the left of its container with the float property: <code>float: right</code></p>
                                            <strong>Example</strong><br />
                                            <a class="btn btn-danger pull-right clearfix" href="#" style="margin-right: 8px;"> A button with pull right</a>
                                            <a class="btn btn-danger" href="#"> A button</a>
                                            <pre class="prettyprint linenums m1" style="margin-bottom: 18px;">&lt;a class="btn btn-danger pull-right" href="#"&gt; A button with pull-right&lt;/a&gt;</pre>
                                        </div>
                                    </div><!-- end .row -->
                        <h5>Text position</h5>
                            <p>For the text alignment, two classes were created:</p>
                                    <div class="row">
                                        <div class="span5">
                                            <h5>center <code>class="center"</code></h5>
                                            <p>This class centers the text with the text-align property: <code>text-align: center</code></p>
                                            <h5>Example</h5>
                                            <p>Some text...Mauris auctor vestibulum lorem, eu accumsan ante lobortis ut.
                                            Duis commodo orci urna. Cras et neque ut purus dapibus interdum. Sed sit amet turpis leo. Aliquam erat volutpat.</p>
                                            <p>With <code>class="center"</code>:</p>
											<div class="well">
												<p class="center">Some text...Mauris auctor vestibulum lorem, eu accumsan ante lobortis ut.
												Duis commodo orci urna. Cras et neque ut purus dapibus interdum. Sed sit amet turpis leo. Aliquam erat volutpat.</p>
											</div>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="span5">
                                            <h5>justify <code>class="justify"</code></h5>
                                            <p>This class put the text in justified (the sentences go to the end of the container
                                                and the spacing increases) with text-align property: <code>text-align: justify</code></p>
                                            <h5>Example</h5>
                                            <p>Some text...Mauris auctor vestibulum lorem, eu accumsan ante lobortis ut.
                                            Duis commodo orci urna. Cras et neque ut purus dapibus interdum. Sed sit amet turpis leo. Aliquam erat volutpat.</p>
                                            <p>With <code>class="justify"</code>:</p>
											<div class="well">
												<p class="justify">Some text...Mauris auctor vestibulum lorem, eu accumsan ante lobortis ut.
												Duis commodo orci urna. Cras et neque ut purus dapibus interdum. Sed sit amet turpis leo. Aliquam erat volutpat.</p>
											</div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div><!-- end .row -->
                        <h5>Text shadow </h5>
                            <code>class="text_shadow"</code><br />
                                <p>This class adds a shadow on the text with text-shadow: <code>text-shadow: 0px 0px 3px #555;</code></p>
                                <strong>Example</strong>
                                <p>Some text...Mauris auctor vestibulum lorem, eu accumsan ante lobortis ut.
                                Duis commodo orci urna. Cras et neque ut purus dapibus interdum. Sed sit amet turpis leo. Aliquam erat volutpat.</p>
                                <p>With <code>class="justify"</code> et well plus un background bleu pour la demo:</p>
                                <p class="text_shadow well" style="color: #FFF; background: #00afff;">Some text...Mauris auctor vestibulum lorem, eu accumsan ante lobortis ut.
                                Duis commodo orci urna. Cras et neque ut purus dapibus interdum. Sed sit amet turpis leo. Aliquam erat volutpat.</p>
								
						<p>I invite you to look at the documentation of Bootstrap about this topic:<br /><br />
								<a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/components.html#misc" class="btn btn-inverse btn-large" target="_blank"><i class="icon-white icon-ok-sign"></i> Miscellaneous bars with Bootstrap</a></p>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Columns</h3>
						<p>I invite you to look at the documentation of Bootstrap about this topic:<br /><br />
								<a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/scaffolding.html#gridSystem" class="btn btn-inverse btn-large" target="_blank"><i class="icon-white icon-ok-sign"></i> Columns with Bootstrap</a></p>
					</section>
