					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					FAQ's
					///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
					////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////-->
					<section id="faq">
						<div class="page-header">
							<h1>FAQ's <small>frequently asked questions</small></h1> <a href="#" class="scroller pull-right"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
						</div>
						<h3 class="m2" >Why there is no php scripts for the search form and the comment form in the blog ?</h3>
						<blockquote>Because, to use it you need a database MySql and this item is in the "Site template" category not in "Wordpress" so this forms are here if you translate this template in wordpress, joomla, prestashop...(these CMS can manage the operation and design is already there ;) )</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Why I can't load it in Wordpress ?</h3>
						<blockquote>Because, this item is in the "Site template" category not in "Wordpress"...But it's easy to translate it, Google is your friend.</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Why there is only one level for the dropdown menu ?</h3>
						<blockquote>Because, I do not see much use, but I can understand that you need it, if you are patient send me an email and I will add this functionality in the next version ... Otherwise, this plugin do it very well -> <a href="http://users.tpg.com.au/j_birch/plugins/superfish/" target="_blank">Superfish</a>.</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Why Javascript elements do not work ?</h3>
						<blockquote>If for example the dropdowns, tabs, effects "isotope", "prettyPhoto", the slider does not work. Just check if the file is Javascript plugin well known in the page (in the footer.php: <code>&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="..." &gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code>) 
                        Whether because to save time in loading the page, some plugins are not called in every page (much of the available plugins bootstrap for example, feel free to add).</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >How to adapt my image with wrong size ?</h3>
						<blockquote>You'll notice that each image site requires precise size so that there was no display bugs...So you just have to resize your images at the good size or to trim it with Photoshop or Paint.</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Sometimes I see tasks appear black (seen in Google Chrome)</h3>
						<blockquote>The problem is coming with Tooltip effect if it's problematic for you delete the file <code>bootstrap-tooltip.js</code>.</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Slider in the home pages doesn't work...</h3>
						<blockquote>After including <code>slider_1.php</code> or <code>slider_2.php</code>, they do not always work...Check if <code>style_slider.css</code> is called in the top of your page.</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Elements disappear on my Ipad, Iphone..</h3>
						<blockquote>Example, the map in the contact page disappear on  your Iphone, why it's a choice (this is not practical, not for this), it's the same thing for the slider. But you're free to go into <code>style_responsive.css</code>, <code>style_slider.css</code> and change it.</blockquote>
						
						<h3 class="m2" >Where can I find help ?</h3>
                        <blockquote>Feel free to ask me questions on my profil page in ThemeForest, or send me an email: <strong>help@2f-design.fr</strong></blockquote>
					</section>
